cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on adapting pretrained models for natural language processing (NLP) tasks, which is a common topic in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of transfer learning and fine-tuning, which are also relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper's empirical results also include experiments on image captioning, which could place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the paper's exploration of possible explanations for their findings could relate to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
